devdoc.details: Interface for any contract that wants to support safeTransfers from ERC721X contracts.

onERC721XBatchReceived(address,address,u.details: Handle the receipt of multiple fungible tokens from an MFT contract. The ERC721X smart contract calls this function on the recipient after a `batchTransfer`. This function MAY throw to revert and reject the transfer. Return of other than the magic value MUST result in the transaction being reverted. Returns `bytes4(keccak256("onERC721XBatchReceived(address,address,uint256[],uint256[],bytes)"))` unless throwing.

params._amounts: Array of amount of object per type to be transferred.
params._data: Additional data with no specified format.
params._from: The address from which the token was transfered from.
params._types: Array of types of token being transferred (where each type is represented as an ID)

devdoc.title: ERC721X token receiver interface

onERC721XBatchReceived(address,address,u.notice: The contract address is always the message sender. A wallet/broker/auction application MUST implement the wallet interface if it will accept safe transfers.
